00:23:02.046 --> 00:23:03.806 A:middle
And then let's go
ahead and call it

00:23:03.806 --> 00:23:04.816 A:middle
from the interface controller.

00:23:11.146 --> 00:23:12.786 A:middle
So we are taking
the sandwich image,

00:23:13.426 --> 00:23:15.466 A:middle
we are calling Set Accessibility
Image Regions on it,

00:23:15.956 --> 00:23:17.366 A:middle
or the generated image regions.

00:23:17.886 --> 00:23:21.666 A:middle
Now, the second issue
we had here was

00:23:21.726 --> 00:23:24.646 A:middle
that the information button
only being spoken as "i."

00:23:25.136 --> 00:23:27.436 A:middle
Since the label doesn't change
at all throughout the lifecycle

00:23:27.436 --> 00:23:28.306 A:middle
of the information button,

00:23:28.636 --> 00:23:30.146 A:middle
we can simply set it
in the Storyboard.

00:23:30.706 --> 00:23:33.236 A:middle
Let's select that
information button.

00:23:33.766 --> 00:23:37.976 A:middle
Let's go ahead and set the
label to be "information."

00:23:38.506 --> 00:23:40.176 A:middle
Like so. Okay.

00:23:44.556 --> 00:23:46.956 A:middle
So now we fixed that label.

00:23:46.956 --> 00:23:49.236 A:middle
But the other issue we had
with the information button was

00:23:49.236 --> 00:23:51.346 A:middle
that it wasn't large
enough for a VoiceOver user

00:23:51.346 --> 00:23:52.876 A:middle
to easily feel on screen.

00:23:53.286 --> 00:23:55.896 A:middle
So we need to resize it based
on whether VoiceOver is running.

00:23:55.896 --> 00:23:57.906 A:middle
So I am going to add
a function to do that.

00:23:58.406 --> 00:24:04.086 A:middle
What this is doing is it checks
whether VoiceOver is running

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:23:58.406 --> 00:24:04.086 A:middle
What this is doing is it checks
whether VoiceOver is running

00:24:04.256 --> 00:24:06.586 A:middle
with a WK Accessibility
Is VoiceOver Running call,

00:24:07.416 --> 00:24:09.656 A:middle
and if it is, it sets the
height and width to be 40.

00:24:09.946 --> 00:24:11.186 A:middle
Otherwise it sets it to be 20.

00:24:11.886 --> 00:24:17.436 A:middle
Now, we have to call this on
Will Activate, so this ...

00:24:32.856 --> 00:24:35.686 A:middle
And also, just in case someone
turns VoiceOver on while

00:24:35.686 --> 00:24:37.676 A:middle
on this screen, we should
go ahead and register

00:24:37.676 --> 00:24:42.726 A:middle
for the notification and
have it call this function.

00:24:43.456 --> 00:24:46.936 A:middle
Notification is WK accessibility
VoiceOver status changed.

00:24:48.176 --> 00:24:52.806 A:middle
Now, let's see our fixed
application in action.

00:24:54.546 --> 00:24:54.716 A:middle
&gt;&gt; VOICEOVER: Eats.

00:24:54.876 --> 00:24:56.696 A:middle
Eats fixed.

00:24:57.526 --> 00:25:04.156 A:middle
Eats fixed.

