00:26:22.266 --> 00:26:26.056 A:middle
&gt;&gt; QASID SADIQ: Now, as you
guys know, you, as developers,

00:26:26.056 --> 00:26:28.926 A:middle
now have the ability to
make your own custom clock

00:26:28.926 --> 00:26:29.916 A:middle
face Complications.

00:26:30.616 --> 00:26:34.756 A:middle
And just like your applications,
these need to be accessible too.

00:26:34.966 --> 00:26:38.206 A:middle
Now, our frameworks can
determine an accessibility label

00:26:38.206 --> 00:26:40.986 A:middle
for most complications, but
there are a couple situations

00:26:40.986 --> 00:26:43.756 A:middle
where that accessibility
label may be misrepresentative

00:26:43.756 --> 00:26:45.516 A:middle
or nonexistent.

00:26:46.376 --> 00:26:49.176 A:middle
You see, each clock face
Complication is composed

00:26:49.176 --> 00:26:53.086 A:middle
of a set of image and text
providers, and although most

00:26:53.086 --> 00:26:56.516 A:middle
of these providers have very
obvious accessibility labels

00:26:56.516 --> 00:27:00.976 A:middle
associated with them,
a couple don't.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:26:56.516 --> 00:27:00.976 A:middle
associated with them,
a couple don't.

00:27:00.976 --> 00:27:02.836 A:middle
Image provider and
Simple Text provider.

00:27:03.506 --> 00:27:05.686 A:middle
So for these two
particular providers,

00:27:05.686 --> 00:27:09.086 A:middle
we've added a property,
Accessibility Label.

00:27:10.396 --> 00:27:13.146 A:middle
This works just like the
accessibility label does

00:27:13.146 --> 00:27:14.756 A:middle
on a normal WatchKit
application,

00:27:15.406 --> 00:27:16.466 A:middle
and it's actually pretty easy.

00:27:17.186 --> 00:27:25.856 A:middle
So I made a complication to
make it really easy for you

00:27:25.856 --> 00:27:27.656 A:middle
to order a sandwich, just in
case you are really hungry

00:27:27.656 --> 00:27:29.516 A:middle
that you don't have time
to open the application.

00:27:29.516 --> 00:27:31.276 A:middle
You simply want to
lift your wrist

00:27:31.476 --> 00:27:32.816 A:middle
and get a sandwich right now.

00:27:32.966 --> 00:27:35.296 A:middle
So this is the Complication
right here.

00:27:35.706 --> 00:27:36.516 A:middle
And since it's an image,

00:27:36.516 --> 00:27:39.306 A:middle
it has no accessibility
label associated with it.

00:27:39.666 --> 00:27:42.586 A:middle
So let's go ahead and actually
set an accessibility label

00:27:42.706 --> 00:27:43.306 A:middle
on it.

00:27:47.116 --> 00:27:53.306 A:middle
So we go to wherever the
Complication is created,

00:27:54.516 --> 00:27:55.646 A:middle
or the provider is created.

00:27:56.146 --> 00:27:58.436 A:middle
And we set an accessibility
label.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:28:05.416 --> 00:28:06.196 A:middle
And there you go.

00:28:07.406 --> 00:28:07.986 A:middle
It's that easy.

00:28:08.966 --> 00:28:11.886 A:middle
So let's see how a
VoiceOver user will hear this.

00:28:23.876 --> 00:28:25.696 A:middle
&gt;&gt; VOICEOVER: Get sandwich now.

00:28:25.946 --> 00:28:27.246 A:middle
&gt;&gt; QASID SADIQ: So
if you couldn't hear,

00:28:27.566 --> 00:28:29.396 A:middle
the label spoke "get
a sandwich now,"

00:28:29.806 --> 00:28:31.526 A:middle
so now our VoiceOver
users have the ability

00:28:31.906 --> 00:28:35.786 A:middle
to order a sandwich
on a double-tap.

00:28:35.986 --> 00:28:38.756 A:middle
So as you can see, it's
actually really quite easy

00:28:38.756 --> 00:28:41.006 A:middle
to make your applications
and Complications accessible.

00:28:41.006 --> 00:28:43.676 A:middle
Let's talk about a few things
you should keep in mind

00:28:43.676 --> 00:28:45.806 A:middle
when you are designing your
accessibility experience.

00:28:45.856 --> 00:28:49.236 A:middle
First of all, try to make
your images accessible.

00:28:49.856 --> 00:28:51.896 A:middle
Especially if they provide
valuable information

00:28:51.896 --> 00:28:52.496 A:middle
to the user.

00:28:52.496 --> 00:28:54.546 A:middle
You should set an
accessibility label on them.

00:28:55.036 --> 00:28:57.656 A:middle
Or, if they are providing a
very complex set of information,

00:28:57.906 --> 00:28:59.826 A:middle
use the accessibility
image regions API.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:29:03.336 --> 00:29:04.726 A:middle
When you design your
application,

00:29:04.726 --> 00:29:06.236 A:middle
think about how a
VoiceOver user is going

00:29:06.236 --> 00:29:07.476 A:middle
to navigate your screen.

00:29:07.536 --> 00:29:09.696 A:middle
You don't want to make it
so a VoiceOver user has

00:29:09.696 --> 00:29:12.386 A:middle
to swipe several times to
get past one logical item.

00:29:12.826 --> 00:29:15.646 A:middle
So group your accessibility
elements together by using Set

00:29:15.646 --> 00:29:16.766 A:middle
As Accessibility Element.

00:29:17.396 --> 00:29:21.396 A:middle
Now, this is probably true for
non-VoiceOver users as well,

00:29:21.396 --> 00:29:23.336 A:middle
but you should avoid
tiny interface items.

00:29:23.926 --> 00:29:27.066 A:middle
It's difficult for a
VoiceOver user to feel

00:29:27.096 --> 00:29:29.556 A:middle
and find a tiny interface
item on screen.

00:29:31.316 --> 00:29:33.286 A:middle
Finally, most importantly,

00:29:33.866 --> 00:29:35.676 A:middle
try accessibility
on your application.

00:29:36.176 --> 00:29:38.506 A:middle
See what your application looks
like with increased text size.

00:29:38.956 --> 00:29:41.996 A:middle
Or, see how your application
works with VoiceOver on.

00:29:42.496 --> 00:29:43.926 A:middle
You might be surprised
at what you find.

00:29:44.536 --> 00:29:50.936 A:middle
In conclusion, the Apple Watch
is quite an accessible device.

00:29:51.466 --> 00:29:54.396 A:middle
But for it to be
completely accessible,

00:29:54.396 --> 00:29:56.256 A:middle
it needs to have
accessible apps.

00:29:57.036 --> 00:29:59.426 A:middle
This is where you guys really
get to be the champions

00:29:59.426 --> 00:30:00.706 A:middle
of our VoiceOver users.

WEBVTT
